---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { site } from "../lib/site.ts";

const portrait = "/photos/about/aaron-photographing.jpg";
---

<BaseLayout title="About">
  <article class="mx-auto grid max-w-6xl gap-12 px-6 pt-16 pb-24 sm:px-8 sm:pt-24 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1fr)_1.4fr] lg:gap-20 lg:px-12">
    <figure class="lg:sticky lg:top-12 lg:self-start">
      <div class="aspect-[4/5] w-full overflow-hidden bg-stone-200">
        <img
          src={portrait}
          alt="Portrait — Aaron Thompson Photography"
          class="h-full w-full object-cover"
        />
      </div>
    </figure>

    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.22em] text-stone-500">About</p>
      <h1 class="mt-4 font-display text-4xl font-light leading-tight text-stone-900 sm:text-5xl">
        I’ve been a portrait photographer for 25 years.
      </h1>

      <div class="mt-10 space-y-6 text-base leading-relaxed text-stone-700 sm:text-lg">
        <p>
          I’m a Philadelphia area portrait photographer specializing in the intimate,
          candid moments between poses. From the glance that passes between a bride and
          groom to the little gesture of a mother brushing her son’s hair out of his eyes,
          these are the pictures that stay with you.
        </p>
        <p>
          Three years ago, my family made the decision to move from Utah to Delco. My
          teenagers didn’t love the transition at first, but I immediately fell in love
          with this area. Philly is amazing. People are rightfully proud of who they are,
          and they don’t pretend to be something they aren’t. I’ve always appreciated the
          genuine, which is why you’ll see it in every photo I create.
        </p>
        <p>
          More than two decades as a portrait and wedding photographer has taught me that
          people only look natural in pictures when they feel comfortable. The thing is,
          almost everyone is uncomfortable having their photo taken. I don’t take that
          lightly, and the way I work is built around it. I’m easy to talk to. I treat a
          session like a real conversation, and the experience of being photographed feels
          effortless from there. People relax, they actually have fun, and the photographs
          come out looking genuinely like them.
        </p>
        <p>
          As the dad of teenagers, I can tell you time doesn’t slow down. Real photos of
          the people you really love are precious, and I’m proud to capture them for you.
        </p>
        <p>
          Based in Delco — happy to travel for the right session. If you’d like to work
          together,
          <a
            href="/contact"
            class="border-b border-stone-400 pb-px text-stone-900 transition-colors hover:border-stone-900"
          >
            get in touch
          </a>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <dl class="mt-12 grid gap-x-8 gap-y-4 border-t border-stone-200 pt-8 text-sm sm:grid-cols-2">
        <div>
          <dt class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-stone-500">Email</dt>
          <dd class="mt-1">
            <a href={site.emailHref} class="text-stone-800 transition-colors hover:text-stone-900">
              {site.email}
            </a>
          </dd>
        </div>
        <div class="sm:col-span-2">
          <dt class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-stone-500">Service area</dt>
          <dd class="mt-1 text-stone-800">{site.area}</dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
